            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head/>
                <origin>The Georgia Constitutionalist</origin>
                <commentary>The Georgia Constitutionalist possesses a letter by Robert Toombs, late
                    Senator of the U. S. and late rebel Secretary of State. He writes of the
                    "wickedness and corruption of the managers of the bogus Government, and says
                    that the whole rebellion is rotten, useless and wicked."</commentary>
                <excerpt>"Both had powerful and established State Governments to back them. We were
                    united in favor of the war. They were divided. They have kept twice the number
                    of men in the field that we have, upon half the money, and paid their soldiers
                    better than we have."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Reprints an article criticizing the Confederate government.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
